theorem closure_inter_interior_subset_closure_inter {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A : Set X) ∩ interior (B : Set X) ⊆ closure ((A ∩ B) : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  rcases hx with ⟨h_clA, h_intB⟩
  -- We prove `x ∈ closure (A ∩ B)` using the neighbourhood
  -- characterization of the closure.
  apply (Set.mem_closure).2
  intro V hV_open hxV
  -- Intersect the neighbourhood `V` with `interior B`, which is also open.
  have h_open : IsOpen (V ∩ interior (B : Set X)) := hV_open.inter isOpen_interior
  have hx_mem : (x : X) ∈ V ∩ interior B := ⟨hxV, h_intB⟩
  -- Since `x ∈ closure A`, the open set `V ∩ interior B` intersects `A`.
  have h_nonempty : ((V ∩ interior (B : Set X)) ∩ A).Nonempty := by
    have h_closureA := (Set.mem_closure).1 h_clA
    simpa [Set.inter_comm, Set.inter_left_comm, Set.inter_assoc] using
      h_closureA (V ∩ interior (B : Set X)) h_open hx_mem
  -- Extract a witness from the non-empty intersection and show that it lies in
  -- `V ∩ (A ∩ B)`.
  rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, ⟨⟨hyV, hyIntB⟩, hyA⟩⟩
  have hyB : (y : X) ∈ B := interior_subset hyIntB
  exact ⟨y, ⟨hyV, ⟨hyA, hyB⟩⟩⟩

theorem closure_interior_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    closure (interior (Set.univ : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  simp [interior_univ, closure_univ]
